{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = National Audit Office of the People's Republic of China |nativename_a = {{lang|zh-Hans|中华人民共和国审计署}} |nativename_r = {{small|''Zhōnghuá Rénmín Gònghéguó Shěnjìshǔ''}} |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = People's Republic of China National Emblem.svg |seal_width = 150px |seal_caption = [[Emblem of the People's Republic of China]] |formed = 15 September 1983 |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = {{Flagicon|PRC}} [[Mainland China]] |headquarters = [[Beijing]] |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = |minister1_pfo = |chief1_name = [[Hu Zejun]] |chief1_position = Auditor-General |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |agency_type = [[Cabinet (government)|Cabinet]]-level [[Ministries of the People's Republic of China|Department Constituting the State Council]] |parent_agency = [[State Council of the People's Republic of China|State Council]] |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = http://www.cnao.gov.cn/ |footnotes = }} {{Politics of China |expanded = Executive }}
The '''National Audit Office of the People's Republic of China''' ('''NAO''') is the supreme [[audit]] institution in the [[People's Republic of China]]. It was established in 1983 according to the Constitution. It is a [[Ministries of the People's Republic of China|cabinet-level Department]] Constituting the [[State Council of the People's Republic of China|State Council]] (国务院组成部门) and under the leadership of the [[Premier of the People's Republic of China|Premier]].
